Canada’s NDP President Topp Says He Will Run to Succeed Layton as Leader

-- B y   A n d r e w   M a y e d a
-- 
2011-09-12T15:14:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-12/canada-s-ndp-president-topp-says-he-will-run-to-succeed-layton-as-leader.html
Brian Topp, the president of
 Canada ’s New Democratic Party, said today he will run to succeed
the late  Jack Layton  as leader of the country’s biggest
opposition party.  Topp made the comments at a press conference in Ottawa.
Layton died last month after a battle with cancer. In the May 2
general election, Layton led the NDP to capture 103 of the 308
seats in the nation’s House of Commons, the largest seal total
in the party’s history.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Mayeda in Ottawa at 
